/home/erik/go/pkg/mod/github.com/!document!driven!d!x/agent@v0.9.23/.ddx/beads.jsonl:338:{"acceptance":"1. Exported types `ErrHarnessModelIncompatible` and `ErrProfilePinConflict` exist in package `agent` with documented fields and example usage in godoc.\n2. `errors.Is(err, ErrHarnessModelIncompatible)` and `errors.As(err, \u0026e)` both work as expected.\n3. `ResolveRoute(Request{Harness: \"gemini\", Model: \"minimax/minimax-m2.7\"})` returns `ErrHarnessModelIncompatible{Harness: \"gemini\", Model: \"minimax/minimax-m2.7\", SupportedModels: [gemini-2.5-pro, ...]}` — test asserts exact field values.\n4. `ResolveRoute(Request{Profile: \"local\", Harness: \"claude\"})` returns `ErrProfilePinConflict{Profile: \"local\", ConflictingPin: \"Harness=claude\", ProfileConstraint: \"local-only\"}`. Inverse test: `Profile: \"smart\", Harness: \"agent\"` when agent has only local endpoints.\n5. `Execute` surfaces both errors without starting dispatch. Test asserts no provider call is made when the typed error is returned.\n6. Generic \"no viable candidate\" error path still exists for the ambient case (no pins, no eligible candidates). Test asserts it is NOT conflated with the typed errors.\n7. Errors wrap cleanly with `%w` so callers can chain them without losing type info.\n8. godoc entries include at least one example per error describing DDx-side handling.\n9. Depends on agent-bab52778 (allow-list gating) — that bead must land first so this bead has a concrete condition to trigger on.","claimed-at":"2026-04-22T21:49:03Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"2792459","closing_commit_sha":"5992c7b574bbd7f3deda2e57e65fe4cf28b50baa","created_at":"2026-04-22T21:35:32.002266432Z","description":"## Motivation\n\nGoal G3 from the DDx consumer: \"`--harness claude --model opus-4.7` must be either serviceable or a clean typed error — never a silent substitution.\" Today `ResolveRoute` returns a generic `fmt.Errorf(\"no viable routing candidate: ...\")` string for both \"no eligible provider exists\" (recoverable) and \"the user's explicit pins contradict each other\" (unrecoverable). Callers can't distinguish.\n\n## Scope\n\nAdd two typed errors exported from package `agent`:\n\n- `ErrHarnessModelIncompatible` — returned when caller pins both `Harness` and `Model` and the harness's allow-list does not include the model (after the new gating from agent-bab52778 lands). Includes structured fields: `Harness`, `Model`, `SupportedModels []string`.\n- `ErrProfilePinConflict` — returned when caller's explicit `Profile` constraint contradicts explicit `Harness` or `Model` pin (e.g., `Profile: \"local\", Harness: \"claude\"` when claude is non-local). Includes: `Profile`, ConflictingPin (Harness or Model), ProfileConstraint (short description).\n\nBoth errors wrap `error` via standard `errors.Is / errors.As` support.\n\n`ResolveRoute` and `Execute` both surface these errors unchanged. DDx-side preflight (tracked in `ddx-fdd3ea36`) uses `errors.As` to extract the structured fields for the bead's failure record and for the worker log.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- `internal/routing/engine.go` Resolve: distinguish \"no viable\" (ambient) from \"explicit pin conflict\" (caller error) when returning the error. The engine has enough info in `Request` and the rejected candidates to make this call.\n- `service_routing.go` ResolveRoute: propagate the typed error unchanged.\n- `service_execute.go` Execute: when pre-resolution surfaces the typed error, return it unchanged to the caller without starting any dispatch.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-04-22T22:01:01.3250335Z","kind":"routing","source":"ddx agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260422T214903-97b32799\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"input_tokens\":7526616,\"output_tokens\":26307,\"total_tokens\":7552923,\"cost